    "53-year-old woman with flushing and itching -Correctly identifies niacin-induced flushing as the most likely cause.",
    "-Considers other possibilities (carcinoid, pheochromocytoma, allergy).",
    "-Understands the limitations of statins and fibrates.",
    "-Recognizes the need for LDL management.",
    "-Incorrectly prioritizes switching to fenofibrate over managing niacin side effects."
